OL,6,FCouncillor Gordon Wheeler, Deputy
OL,7,FCabinet Member for Communities and
OL,8,FPublic Health at Nottinghamshire
OL,9,FCounty Council, said: "If you or
OL,10,Fsomeone you know owns and uses an
OL,11,Felectric blanket, don't delay spending
OL,12,Fjust a few minutes checking it for the
OL,13,Fkey signs of wear.
OL,15,F"Your blanket doesn't have to meet all
OL,16,Fof the 10 points listed above to mean
OL,17,Fit needs replacing ` even just having
OL,18,Fone of these signs of wear means that
OL,19,Fyour blanket shouldn't be used any
OL,20,Ffurther."
